ret:
Based on the three observing views (front, side/back, and interface-level functional views) described in the documentation, the eReader should have the following buttons and interfaces:

1. **Front View Buttons & Interfaces**: 
- Home/ESC button (for exiting current interface or canceling operations);
- Prev/Next Page buttons (for page navigation);
- Navigation/Menu button (4-way directional control + menu/confirm function);
- Zoom In/Out button (for JPEG zooming and font size adjustment);
- Rotate button (for screen orientation switching);
- Play/Pause button (for audio playback/recording);
- Volume Up (+) and Volume Down (−) buttons;
- 7″ TFT LCD Display Screen (800×480 resolution) showing main menu, battery indicator, USB connection status, etc.

2. **Side/Back View Interfaces**: 
- Power button (3–5 sec press to power on/off);
- 3.5 mm Earphone Jack;
- USB Port (Mini USB, v2.0);
- Micro SD card reader (supports up to 16GB SD/SDHC);
- Reset On/Off switch (located on the back next to the card reader);
- Speaker (0.5W output).

3. **Logical/Software Interface View**: 
- Main Menu interface with icons/options for: Browser History, eBook, Music, Video, Photo, Record, Explorer, Settings;
- USB Connection mode interface (auto-activated when connected to PC, shows as two Removable Disks: internal memory + microSD);
- Battery indicator (upper right of main menu);
- Charging status icon (displayed during USB charging);
- System-level interfaces for firmware upgrade, file management, and troubleshooting prompts.
